# Documentation Guidelines

## Code Documentation:

- Add godoc comments for all exported types and functions
- Include usage examples in documentation comments
- Document complex algorithms and business logic
- Keep comments up-to-date with code changes

## README Structure:

- Include project description and purpose
- Add installation and usage instructions
- Document prerequisites and dependencies
- Provide examples and common use cases
- Include troubleshooting section

## API Documentation:

- Document CRD fields and their purposes
- Include validation rules and constraints
- Provide examples of valid resources
- Document status fields and their meanings

## Development Documentation:

- Document build and test procedures
- Include contribution guidelines
- Document local development setup
- Add debugging and troubleshooting guides

## Changelog and Releases:

- Maintain clear changelog with versions
- Document breaking changes prominently
- Include upgrade instructions
- Follow semantic versioning

## Comments in Code:

- Explain "why" not "what" in comments
- Document non-obvious design decisions
- Add TODO comments for future improvements
- Use proper comment formatting for tools
